{
  "_schemaVersion": 2,
  "_notes": [
    "Single source of truth for document type identity, routing, required",
    "clauses, per-doctype max_tokens, jurisdiction variants, and worker",
    "classification modes. Replaces lib/doc-completeness-spec.json (v1).",
    "",
    "Accessors live in lib/doc-registry.js — do NOT import this JSON from",
    "anywhere else. Endpoint code must use typed accessors (getTitle,",
    "getBodyTemplate, etc.), never string-parse this file.",
    "",
    "Structure:",
    "  bodyTemplates[id]           → { declared_title }",
    "  docTypes[id] contains       → { id, title, body_template_id,",
    "                                  required_clauses, max_tokens,",
    "                                  jurisdiction_variants,",
    "                                  worker_classification_modes,",
    "                                  forbidden_titles }",
    "  jurisdiction_variants[key]  → { title, body_template_id }",
    "",
    "INVARIANT enforced by assertRegistryConsistent() at module load:",
    "  For every docType × jurisdiction_variant, the resolved",
    "  body_template_id must exist in bodyTemplates AND its declared_title",
    "  must equal the variant's title. Bad merges fail server boot.",
    "",
    "worker_classification_modes is defined here but unused until Phase 5",
    "(per amendment). Populated for employment-adjacent doc types so the",
    "schema is ready; empty array for types where classification doesn't",
    "apply.",
    "",
    "forbidden_titles is consumed by the DOC_TITLE_BODY_MISMATCH detector",
    "in lib/doc-completeness.js. Entries are titles of legally-distinct",
    "document types that must never appear in this doc's body. Scope them",
    "tightly — too many false positives will suppress valid output."
  ],
  "defaults": {
    "max_tokens": 8000
  },
  "bodyTemplates": {
    "service_agreement_v1":        { "declared_title": "Service Agreement" },
    "service_agreement_ng_v1":     { "declared_title": "Service Agreement" },
